name: LevelEvent.Unload
description: This event is fired whenever a level unloads. This event is fired whenever a level unloads in Minecraft.setLevel(ClientLevel) , MinecraftServer.stopServer() , Minecraft.clearLevel(Screen) , and ForgeInternalHandler.onDimensionUnload(Unload) . This event is not cancellable and does not have a result. This event is fired on the main Forge event bus on both logical sides.
